SLM install

- Move scripts directory into /home/user/srcds

- Update scripts/globals.sh with path to srcds directory (e.g. /home/cs/srcds)

- Create server configs under cfg/ directory (e.g. server1.cfg, server2.cfg)

- Append to svn_update script the servers you wish to restart after SVN update. Example:

#Individual servers
/home/gmod/srcds/scripts/update.sh construct server_construct.cfg
/home/gmod/srcds/scripts/update.sh build server_build.cfg

- Add check.sh and svn_update.sh crontabs. Example:

*/2  *    * * *   gmod    /home/gmod/srcds/scripts/check.sh construct server_construct.cfg
*/2  *    * * *   gmod    /home/gmod/srcds/scripts/check.sh build server_build.cfg
30  7    * * *   gmod    /home/gmod/srcds/scripts/svn_update.sh

The check script runs every two minutes, svn_update script runs at 0730 each day.

- Update the create.sh and svn_update.sh scripts to tailor to your needs.
